# Line-ending policy.
#
# This workspace is developed and deployed on Linux, and its text is parsed
# assuming LF end-of-line throughout:
#   - vendored script embedded at compile time via include_str!
#     (drivers/ur-robot/src/rtde_control.script — its injection anchors match
#     on "\n"),
#   - EPICS iocsh startup scripts (st.cmd, *.cmd — iocsh, not Windows batch),
#   - db / template / proto / substitutions record files.
#
# Force LF on checkout on every platform so a Windows checkout with
# core.autocrlf=true cannot inject CRLF and break LF-sensitive parsing (this is
# what failed the ur-robot script test on the Windows CI cells). text=auto lets
# git leave genuine binaries untouched; eol=lf pins the working-tree EOL for
# everything it classifies as text.
* text=auto eol=lf
